_sw_menu_swpns="To set the swappiness permanently"
_free_info="View your computer's RAM"
_msg_swps_title="How often to use the swap partition"
_swap_frequency_info="The frequency of usage of the paging file 'swap'"
_sw_nfo1="Swappiness sysctl parameter represents the frequency\nthe use of swap space."
_sw_nfo2="Swappiness can have a value from 0 to 100."
_sw_nfo3="The default value is 60."
_sw_nfo4="This means that when the RAM consumption reaches 40%,\nthe Linux kernel activates the swap application."
_sw_nfo5="When the value of swappiness = 10 -\nRAM consumption will reach 90%."
_sw_nfo6="And when swappiness = 90 -\nRAM consumption will not exceed 10%."
_sw_nfo7="A low value causes the kernel to avoid paging,\na high value allows the kernel to use paging in advance."
_sw_nfo8="The use of low values at a sufficient number of memory,\nimproves responsiveness on many systems."

